What you need to know:

Cassava cuttings should be obtained from mature stems from plants that are nine to 18 months, long enough with at least five nodes.In mono-cropping, the recommended spacing is a square arrangement, 1m by 1m giving 10,000 plants per hectare or 4,000 plants per acre.According to Dr Munga, cassava is a hardy crop and has an extensive root system that enables it to grow in poor soils.Harvesting can be mechanically done using a pull harvester attached to a tractor.Â 